body.description: Puressentiel Organic Intimate Hygiene Gentle Cleansing Gel is an ultra-gentle soap-free cleansing base with physiological pH that delicately cleanses while respecting the sensitivity and balance of intimate areas. It has been specially formulated for mucous membranes and sensitive skin. It offers everyday protection against discomfort in intimate areas. Its formula is 99,6% Natural, Certified Organic by Ecocert, Vegan and Cruelty Free : three organic floral waters (Damask rose, Roman chamomile and sage), organic essential oils (tea tree, true lavender) and organic aloe vera, with soothing refreshing and hydrating properties. Use every day as a liquid soap for external use when cleansing intimate areas. Lather and then rinse thoroughly with water after application. Specially formulated to be hypoallergenic and free of soap, artificial fragrances and artificial coloring. Its excellent tolerance has been gynaecologically tested.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lets you be you
reviews.reviewText: As you can see, this is a clear gel. The product is made in France, it's a Belgian company.It seems that so many Europeans have a better understanding in terms of skin care. A woman's intimate area has a different pH and requires a different cleanser for optimal health. The key word is optimal, of course other soaps and cleansers aren't going to hurt you.That being said I really like using a product like this that I know is not going to have any irritation. If you're the certain person that can't take bubble baths because they will irritate you, and you need unscented soaps for your intimate area, you're going to love this cleanser. It's not one of those ones that gets all foamy and gets bubbles in your, well, places where you don't want bubbly irritants. I've traced a UTI back to a perfumed soap.Great list of ingredients including botanicals.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Gentle Intimate Cleanser With No Scent
reviews.reviewText: This hygiene wash doe a good job of gentle/thorough cleaning, but I wish its scent was a bit more noticeable. It’s advertised as having three floral water (damask rose, chamomile and sage) ingredients as well as two oils (tea tree and lavender), so you’d think there would be some scent. To me it’s odorless. I’ll use this up, but will return to less expensive hygiene products that work just as well, but also provide soft feminine scents.

reviews.reviewTitle: Suave y cuidadoso con la piel, dejando sensación de frescor
reviews.reviewText: Este gel limpiador es suave, y está especialmente indicado para las mucosas y la piel sensible, además limpia y protege con delicadeza, respetando la sensibilidad y el equilibrio de las partes íntimas. Viene en una caja con la imagen de la marca y del producto, que indica sus ingredientes, características y modo de uso, el envase interior es un bote cilíndrico de plástico, que contiene 250ml. Su composición es en un 99,6% de origen natural e incluye tres aguas florales y aloe vera. Debido a su pH fisiológico puede usarse a diario. Es hipoalergénico, sin jabón, sin parabenos, sin colorantes, ni perfume de síntesis. Tiene certificado BIO y ha sido testado bajo control dermatológico.Al extraer parte del producto, ves que es un gel transparente de poca densidad y fácil de usar, el modo de usarlo es humedecerlo con un poco de agua y hace algo de espuma, después de aplicarlo hay que aclarar con agua abundante. El aroma es entre herbal y floral, y muy agradable, dejando sensación de frescor, hidratación y confort durante muchas horas. Puedes usarlo a diario y también como gel corporal.
